const faqItems = [
  {
    question: 'Is ProProfs Chat free?',
    answer: 'ProProfs Chat offers a free forever plan for single operators with limited features — basic live chat, chat widget, and basic reporting. Paid plans start at around $19.99/month (Team plan) for multiple operators, chatbots, advanced routing, and CRM integrations. A 15-day free trial is available for all paid plans with no credit card required. The free plan is useful for very small businesses testing live chat.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What are ProProfs Chat\'s pricing plans?',
    answer: 'ProProfs Chat offers three main tiers: Free (1 operator, basic features), Team (~$19.99/month per operator, includes chatbots, routing, and integrations), and Business (custom pricing for large teams with advanced analytics, SLAs, and dedicated support). Annual billing typically saves 30% over monthly. Note: pricing may vary by region and is subject to change — verify current pricing on proprofs.com/chat.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does ProProfs Chat have AI chatbot features?',
    answer: 'Yes. ProProfs Chat includes an AI chatbot builder on paid plans that can handle common queries, qualify leads, route conversations, and provide 24/7 automated responses when agents are offline. The chatbot uses rule-based flows and can be trained on your FAQ content. For more sophisticated AI (natural language understanding, GPT-level responses), you would need a separate AI layer or integration.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How does ProProfs Chat compare to Zendesk?',
    answer: 'ProProfs Chat is significantly more affordable than Zendesk for small to mid-size teams (starting at ~$20/operator/month vs Zendesk\'s $55+/agent/month for comparable features). ProProfs is simpler to set up and better for businesses primarily focused on live chat. Zendesk has a more comprehensive support suite (ticketing, email, voice, social), better enterprise scalability, and a larger integration marketplace. For focused live chat needs on a budget, ProProfs wins. For a full omnichannel support platform, Zendesk is more mature.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can ProProfs Chat integrate with CRM systems?',
    answer: 'Yes. ProProfs Chat integrates with major CRMs including Salesforce, HubSpot, Zoho CRM, and Pipedrive. It also integrates with Slack, Shopify, WordPress, Magento, and 50+ other tools via native connectors and Zapier. API access is available on Business plans for custom integrations. Most native CRM integrations can be configured without developer assistance in under 30 minutes.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is ProProfs Chat good for small businesses?',
    answer: 'ProProfs Chat is well-suited for small businesses, particularly e-commerce, SaaS, and service businesses that want to add live chat without enterprise complexity. The free plan accommodates solo operators and very small teams. The Team plan provides a professional feature set at a small-business-friendly price point. Setup takes under an hour, and the interface is accessible to non-technical users.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How many agents can use ProProfs Chat simultaneously?',
    answer: 'ProProfs Chat supports unlimited concurrent agent sessions on paid plans — there is no cap on simultaneous active chats per account. Each "seat" is a named operator/agent who can log in. You pay per seat, not per concurrent session. The platform can handle high chat volumes through intelligent routing and queuing, distributing conversations across available agents.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does ProProfs Chat support multiple languages?',
    answer: 'Yes. ProProfs Chat\'s chat widget and pre-chat forms can be configured in multiple languages. Agents can chat in any language. The chatbot flows can be localized per language. For automated translation within the chat interface (real-time translation for agents and visitors), you would need to integrate with a translation API. The platform supports RTL (right-to-left) languages for Arabic and Hebrew deployments.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the setup time for ProProfs Chat?',
    answer: 'Basic setup (installing the widget, creating your first agent account, and customizing the chat widget design) takes under 30 minutes. Full setup including CRM integration, chatbot flows, routing rules, and team training typically takes 1–5 business days. ProProfs provides onboarding assistance and a resource library for self-guided setup. No developer resources are required for standard deployments.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What are the best ProProfs Chat alternatives?',
    answer: 'Top alternatives to ProProfs Chat include: Intercom (best for product-led growth and SaaS companies), Zendesk Chat (best for omnichannel support at scale), Freshchat (best price-to-feature ratio), Tidio (best for e-commerce with built-in AI chatbot), LiveChat (best user experience and design), and Crisp (best free plan). For AI-first customer service, explore platforms built on GPT-4o or Claude. See our full enterprise AI chatbot guide for a broader comparison.',
  },
];
